"Hernández F., Gual M.Á., Del Río P., Caparrós A.","Energy sustainability and global warming in Spain",2004,"Energy Policy","32","3",,"383","394",,,10.1016/S0301-4215(02)00308-7,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-17444436900&partnerID=40&md5=8b6759c38844ee494de008433cce6d3a","Instituto de Economia y Geografia, Consejo Sup.de Invest.Cie.(IEG-CSIC), C/Pinar 25, Madrid 28006, Spain; Fac.de Cie.Jur.y Soc.de Toledo, Universidad de Castilla-La Mancha, C/Cobertizo de S. Pedro Martir s/n, Toledo 45071, Spain; Ctr. Intl. de Recherche sur, l'Envrn./le Devmt.(CIRED-CNRS-SMASH), 45 Bis, av. de la Belle Gabrielle, Nogent/Marne 94736, France","Hernández, F., Instituto de Economia y Geografia, Consejo Sup.de Invest.Cie.(IEG-CSIC), C/Pinar 25, Madrid 28006, Spain; Gual, M.Á., Instituto de Economia y Geografia, Consejo Sup.de Invest.Cie.(IEG-CSIC), C/Pinar 25, Madrid 28006, Spain; Del Río, P., Fac.de Cie.Jur.y Soc.de Toledo, Universidad de Castilla-La Mancha, C/Cobertizo de S. Pedro Martir s/n, Toledo 45071, Spain; Caparrós, A., Ctr. Intl. de Recherche sur, l'Envrn./le Devmt.(CIRED-CNRS-SMASH), 45 Bis, av. de la Belle Gabrielle, Nogent/Marne 94736, France","A set of Directives and official documents aim to reorient European policy strategies in the energy sector. However, certain socio-economic and institutional factors prevent Spain from attaining the interrelated goals set up in those documents (namely, energy liberalisation, reduction of CO2 emissions and promotion of renewable energy). These objectives are difficult to achieve in an institutional setting, such as the Spanish one, characterised by different administrative levels (national and regional). Competencies and initiatives taken in CO2 emission mitigation through RE deployment are scattered around those government levels and lack of coordination between such administrative levels seems to be a main feature. In other words, the combined attainment of those objectives requires that policy makers coordinate local, institutional and public initiatives and examine their feasibility. This paper explores the main imbalances and coordination problems at the territorial and sector levels concerning the complex relationship between energy (production and consumption) and sustainability in Spain. From the analysis of these issues, relevant policy implications can be inferred. © 2002 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.","Energy sustainability; Policy coordination; Renewable energy sources (RES)","Carbon dioxide; Economic and social effects; Energy utilization; Global warming; Public policy; Renewable energy resources; Sustainable development; Energy liberalization; Electric power generation; carbon sequestration; emission control; energy policy; environmental economics; global warming; sustainability; Spain",,,,,,"(1998) Informe de la Propuesta de Real Decreto Sobre Producción De Enerǵa Por Instalaciones Abastecidas Por Recursos O Fuentes De Enerǵas Renovables, Residuos Y Cogeneración, , Comisión Nacional del Mercado Eléctrico (CNSE), Ref. I 029/98. Consejo de Administración de la CNSE. 14 de julio de 1998, Madrid; (1998) Green Paper on Greenhouse Emissions Trading in the European Union, , European Commission, Brussels; The shared analysis project (1999) European Union Energy Outlook to 2020, , European Commission, Directorate-General for Energy, Brussels; (1999) Proposal for a Directive of the European Parliament and of the Council on the Promotion of Electricity from Renewable Energy Sources in the Internal Electricity Market, , European Commission, Brussels; (2001) Proposal for a Directive on Establishing a Framework for Greenhouse Gas Emissions Trading Within the European Community, 581. , European Commission, COM (2001) Brussels; (2001) Information Sheet October 2001, , European Environment Agency, Copenhague; Gual, M.A., Hernández, F., Del Rio, P., Certificados Verdes Negociables (CVNs). Una alternativa coherente para promocionar la electricidad a partir de Fuentes de Energía Renovables (E-FER) (2001) Energía, 157, pp. 75-82; (2002) Bolet́n No 4, Eficiencia Energética Y Energías Renovables, , IDAE, Ministerio de Ciencia y Tecnoloǵa (IDAE), Madrid; (2001) Boletines Mensuales de Estad́stica de Producción Y Consumo De Energía Primaria Y Final, , http://www.ine.es/tempus/cgi-bin/itie, INE, Madrid; (2001) Effects of Burden Sharing and Certificate Trade on the Renewable Electricity Market in Europe, , Renewable Energy Burden Sharing project (REBUS), ECN-C-01-030, Amsterdam; (2001) The Marrakech Accords and Declaration, , UNFCCC","Hernández, F.; Instituto de Economia y Geografia, Consejo Sup.de Invest.Cie.(IEG-CSIC), C/Pinar 25, Madrid 28006, Spain; email: felix1@ieg.csic.es",,,,,,,,03014215,,ENPYA,,"English","Energy Policy",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-17444436900
